---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cuba Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/cuba/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Mexico for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/mexico' },
  { title: 'Dominican Republic for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/dominican-republic' },
  { title: 'Jamaica for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/jamaica' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'cubaFit', header: 'Cuba Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$450-645/mo', cubaFit: 'Check Coverage' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$525-750/mo', cubaFit: 'Check Coverage' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$405-580/mo', cubaFit: 'Check Coverage' },
  { provider: 'Asistur (Cuban)', entryAge: 'All ages', renewal: 'Per trip', monthlyFrom: '$3-5/day', cubaFit: 'Required Entry' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'Asistur (Entry Required)', monthly: '$3-5/day', annual: 'Per visit' },
  { category: 'International Supplement (65-69)', monthly: '$405-645', annual: '$4,860-7,740' },
  { category: 'International Supplement (70-74)', monthly: '$555-860', annual: '$6,660-10,320' },
  { category: 'Foreigner Clinic Visit', monthly: 'CUP$50-150/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Evacuation to Mexico', monthly: 'N/A', annual: '$30,000-80,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Cuba 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors visiting Cuba. Time-capsule charm, unique healthcare, US restrictions, and coverage for travelers 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Cuba"
  subheadline="Cuba offers time-capsule Caribbean charm, vintage cars, colonial architecture, famous healthcare system, and unique culture—a fascinating destination with significant travel restrictions and considerations."
  heroImage="/images/countries/cuba-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Important: Cuba Is Complex</h2>
  <p>
    Cuba presents unique challenges for foreign visitors and potential residents. US citizens face strict travel restrictions (12 authorized categories, no tourism). US-based insurance may not cover Cuba due to sanctions. Currency and banking are complicated. Long-term residence is very difficult to obtain.
  </p>

  <p>
    Havana is capital with best infrastructure. Varadero is beach resort area. Trinidad offers colonial charm. Population ~11 million. Mexico (Cancún) is closest backup for medical evacuation. Cuba has good doctors but equipment shortages.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3">Critical Restrictions</h3>
    <ul class="text-red-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>US Citizens:</strong> Tourism technically prohibited; 12 authorized categories only</li>
      <li><strong>US Insurance:</strong> May not cover Cuba due to sanctions—verify carefully</li>
      <li><strong>Banking:</strong> US credit cards don't work; cash required</li>
      <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Very difficult; not typical retirement destination</li>
      <li><strong>Equipment:</strong> Medical equipment shortages due to embargo</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Cuba Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Cuba's healthcare is famous—excellent doctor training, high doctor-to-patient ratios, strong preventive care. However, medical equipment and supplies are limited due to US embargo. Hospitals for foreigners (Cira García in Havana) provide dedicated care but may lack advanced equipment for complex procedures.
  </p>

  <p>
    For serious conditions, evacuation to Mexico (Cancún or Mexico City) is standard. Cuba cannot perform many complex surgeries due to equipment limitations. International insurance with Mexico evacuation essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Good Doctors, Limited Equipment</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Cuban doctors are well-trained and dedicated. However, US embargo causes chronic shortages of medical equipment, medications, and supplies. Complex procedures require evacuation. Don't assume "Cuban healthcare" means all needs are met locally.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options</h2>
  <p>
    Cuba visa/entry options (complicated):
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Card</h3>
  <p>
    30-day tourist entry for most nationalities (except US). Extendable once for 30 more days.
  </p>

  <h3>US Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Must travel under one of 12 authorized categories (support for Cuban people, journalism, professional research, etc.). Tourism is NOT authorized. Documentation required.
  </p>

  <h3>Long-Term Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Very difficult to obtain. Marriage to Cuban citizen, employment, or special government permission required. Not a practical retirement destination for most foreigners.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Cuba:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance MANDATORY for all visitors</li>
    <li><strong>Provider:</strong> Must be from approved Cuban or non-US company</li>
    <li><strong>Asistur:</strong> Cuban insurance available at airport if needed</li>
    <li><strong>US Policies:</strong> May not cover Cuba—verify before travel</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Cuba</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      US citizens: Verify your insurance covers Cuba under OFAC regulations. Non-US citizens: Most international insurers cover Cuba. All visitors need proof of insurance at entry. Asistur (Cuban) insurance available at airport as backup. Mexico evacuation coverage recommended.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For visiting Cuba, verify Cuba coverage before purchase:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Important Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Verify coverage:</strong> Ask specifically about Cuba before purchase</li>
    <li><strong>US restrictions:</strong> US-based insurers may exclude Cuba</li>
    <li><strong>Asistur backup:</strong> Cuban insurance available at entry</li>
    <li><strong>Mexico evacuation:</strong> Ensure coverage for complex cases</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Coverage Information</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Verify Cuba coverage with providers before travel.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Check Cigna Coverage</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Check Allianz Coverage</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Cuba visits (USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry insurance:</strong> Mandatory—budget $3-5/day minimum</li>
    <li><strong>International supplement:</strong> For Mexico evacuation access</li>
    <li><strong>Cash planning:</strong> US cards don't work; plan cash needs</li>
    <li><strong>Living costs:</strong> Very affordable once there</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Canadian Snowbird, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Winter escape to Varadero. 2-month visits. CAD$3,000/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Canadian travel insurance + local Asistur.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$400/month. Affordable beach; Mexico backup if needed.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: US Citizen (Authorized Travel), 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> "Support for Cuban people" category. Short visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Verify US insurer covers Cuba; may need non-US insurer.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$500/month. Ensure OFAC compliance; documentation essential.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: European History Lover, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Extended Cuba exploration. Havana based. €2,500/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> European international insurer + Asistur.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€450/month. Colonial architecture; unique experience.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can US citizens retire to Cuba?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Practically no—US sanctions prohibit tourism, and long-term residence requires marriage to Cuban or special permission. US citizens can visit under authorized categories but cannot simply retire there. Regulations change; check current OFAC rules.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Cuban healthcare really good?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Doctor quality yes; equipment no. Cuban medical education is excellent—many doctors work globally. However, embargo causes chronic shortages of MRI machines, modern medications, surgical supplies. Good for routine care; limited for complex procedures.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How do I handle money in Cuba?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Bring cash—US credit cards don't work. Euros, Canadian dollars, or pounds can be exchanged. Two currencies exist (CUP and MLC). Bring more cash than you think you'll need. ATMs unreliable. This is significant challenge.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What if I need complex medical care?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Evacuation to Mexico—Cancún is closest (1 hour flight). Mexico City has excellent hospitals. Cuba cannot perform many complex surgeries due to equipment limitations. International insurance with Mexico coverage essential.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Consider Easier Alternatives</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Similar Caribbean culture without Cuba's complexity.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/insurance-for/seniors/in/dominican-republic" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Dominican Republic</a>
      <a href="/insurance-for/seniors/in/mexico" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Mexico</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Cuba presents unique challenges including US sanctions, banking restrictions, and visa limitations. This guide is for informational purposes only. US citizens must comply with OFAC regulations. Always verify current requirements and insurance coverage before travel.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
